  <h2>Common Odor Patterns</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Indoors.</strong> Can relate to plumbing traps or venting, or to a system not moving waste along properly.</li>
    <li><strong>Near the tank or lids.</strong> May point to the tank or its access.</li>
    <li><strong>Over the drain field.</strong> Can suggest the field is struggling to absorb wastewater.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Do</h2>
  <p>
    Because similar smells can have different causes, an odor is best treated as a prompt to have the system checked rather than a diagnosis. If odors come with slow drains, gurgling or wet spots, see <a href="/resources/septic-problems/">septic warning signs</a> — or <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a> to have it evaluated.
  </p>

